1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,379
<i>Check the area carefully,</i>
<i>including the sewage system.</i>

2
00:00:04,462 --> 00:00:06,881
<i>Focus on Marcelino Street.</i>

3
00:00:06,965 --> 00:00:09,884
<i>According to Engineer Mike,</i>
<i>the hostage takers will exit from there!</i>

4
00:00:09,968 --> 00:00:12,095
[OFFICER 1]
<i>Positive, sir. They were here.</i>

5
00:00:12,178 --> 00:00:14,055
[OFFICER 2]
<i>Sir, Emil Padua has been found.</i>

6
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:19,185
<i>Patient is male, in his sixties.</i>
<i>Heavy smoke inhalation.</i>

7
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:21,896
<i>Multiple wounds and second-degree burns.</i>

8
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:22,897
<i>He's unconscious.</i>

9
00:00:22,981 --> 00:00:27,027
<i>We need to monitor his blood oxygen</i>
<i>and stabilize his breathing.</i>

10
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:28,945
[LIAM] <i>Doc Jessie. Ma'am Conney.</i>

11
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,030
<i>What happened?</i>

12
00:00:30,113 --> 00:00:31,823
[JESSIE] <i>You lost consciousness, Liam,</i>

13
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:34,451
<i>after escaping from the St. John's fire.</i>

14
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:38,288
<i>You were severely dehydrated.</i>

15
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:39,664
<i>You almost died, son.</i>

16
00:00:39,748 --> 00:00:40,790
<i>Where's Mama?</i>

17
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:43,376
<i>The police are searching for her.</i>

18
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:44,586
[CONNEY] <i>Liam,</i>

19
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:47,630
<i>I hope you don't mind my asking.</i>

20
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,216
<i>Is it true your mom was involved?</i>

21
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,968
<i>But Papa wasn't involved.</i>

22
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:54,387
<i>He had nothing to do with it.</i>

23
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:58,266
<i>If there's anyone who'd know</i>
<i>Greta Roja's whereabouts,</i>

24
00:00:58,349 --> 00:00:59,726
<i>that'd be you, Mr. Roja.</i>

25
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:02,937
<i>If I find out where my wife is hiding,</i>

26
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:05,273
<i>I will surrender her to you myself.</i>

27
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,734
<i>It's confirmed that one of the suspects,</i>

28
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:11,321
<i>Diosdado Menor, died from the fire.</i>

29
00:01:11,404 --> 00:01:14,783
<i>However, some of the suspects</i>
<i>have yet to be captured.</i>

30
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:16,576
<i>These are Homer Sebastian,</i>

31
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:17,619
<i>Gwen Zamora,</i>

32
00:01:17,702 --> 00:01:19,954
<i>Leni Padua, and Lucas Sebastian.</i>

33
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:23,458
<i>Sebastian's wife, Mila Sebastian,</i>
<i>is now in custody.</i>

34
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:26,836
<i>She was allegedly complicit</i>
<i>in the hostage taking.</i>

35
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:30,924
<i>The leader of the group, Emil Padua,</i>
<i>is currently in critical condition.</i>

36
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:34,844
<i>He is currently confined</i>
<i>in a hospital in Alicante.</i>

37
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:39,265
Doc.

38
00:01:39,349 --> 00:01:40,558
[DOOR CLOSES]

39
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:48,566
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:50,985
[PHONE RINGING]

41
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:52,862
[LUNA] <i>How's your patient doing?</i>

42
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:55,281
<i>Keep an eye on him.</i>

43
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:56,491
<i>He is safe.</i>

44
00:01:56,574 --> 00:01:59,244
<i>He's not going anywhere.</i>
<i>He's still comatose.</i>

45
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:01,538
<i>But you still have to be careful.</i>

46
00:02:01,621 --> 00:02:04,207
<i>He might be in a coma, but who knows?</i>

47
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:07,085
<i>His group might be around somewhere.</i>

48
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:11,548
<i>Luna, this is the safest place</i>
<i>in Alicante right now.</i>

49
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:14,509
<i>Half of the police force is here.</i>

50
00:02:14,592 --> 00:02:17,470
Safe? We can never be too sure.

51
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:20,306
Until all of them are caught,
we are not safe.

52
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:22,225
<i>And you.</i>

53
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:24,018
<i>Why did you even volunteer?</i>

54
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:27,313
Why do you have to treat Emil Padua?

55
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:30,150
<i>We can't choose our patients,</i>

56
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:32,402
<i>no matter what or who the patient is.</i>

57
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:34,279
<i>How about you?</i>

58
00:02:34,362 --> 00:02:36,698
<i>How's your patient?</i>

59
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:37,824
Doc.

60
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:40,285
Hello. I'm okay.

61
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:43,163
Doc Jessie said
I'll be discharged tomorrow.

62
00:02:43,246 --> 00:02:44,247
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

63
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:45,707
I'll see you soon.

64
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:48,293
- I'll see you soon, Doc.
- Bye, Ivan.

65
00:02:49,627 --> 00:02:51,671
Do you really want me
to crush your wounds?

66
00:02:51,754 --> 00:02:52,922
[LIAM CHUCKLES]

67
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:57,594
[LIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

68
00:02:57,677 --> 00:02:58,720
[MUSIC FADES]

69
00:03:00,096 --> 00:03:01,347
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

70
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:02,849
What is it?

71
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:05,018
- Uh…
- Let me see that. Come on.

72
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:14,944
That's enough.

73
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:18,239
People are angry at us.

74
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:20,491
Dude,

75
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,493
they don't know anything.

76
00:03:23,202 --> 00:03:25,079
I'm just thinking about Mama.

77
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:26,456
Wherever she is,

78
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:29,667
I just know that she's not safe.

79
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,086
So I hope she surrenders.

80
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:40,637
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

81
00:03:49,437 --> 00:03:56,319
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

82
00:04:27,976 --> 00:04:34,941
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

83
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:51,499
[LUCAS GRUNTS]

84
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:56,838
[BLOWS LAND]

85
00:04:56,921 --> 00:04:59,507
[SIREN BLARING IN DISTANCE]

86
00:05:03,094 --> 00:05:07,890
[MEN PANTING]

87
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:09,225
[GUNS CLICK]

88
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:22,280
[MAN] All clear!

89
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:26,284
[PANTING]

90
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:27,702
Just a false alarm.

91
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:49,599
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

92
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:52,351
[MUSIC FADES]

93
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:56,606
If you ask me,

94
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:58,775
I believe you are innocent,

95
00:05:58,858 --> 00:05:59,901
Mr. Roja.

96
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:03,196
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:04,447
Thank you, Lieutenant.

98
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:08,701
I will do everything I can to find Greta.

99
00:06:09,535 --> 00:06:10,912
Not just to hold her accountable.

100
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:13,122
Not just that.

101
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:15,458
Like I mentioned earlier,
I am worried about her.

102
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,503
Emil Padua's people might have taken her.

103
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:22,965
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:27,595
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

105
00:06:27,678 --> 00:06:29,388
Mr. Roja is here!

106
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:31,015
Folks, Mr. Roja is here!

107
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:32,892
Mr. Roja, how are you?

108
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:35,019
- Attorney, how's it going?
- Give way.

109
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:36,312
Any updates?

110
00:06:38,022 --> 00:06:40,691
- [LIAM] Pa!
- [MAN] Murderer!

111
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:42,819
- Murderer!
- Murderer!

112
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:46,072
- [CAMERAS CLICKING]
- [PEOPLE CLAMORING]

113
00:06:46,155 --> 00:06:48,491
- Bring Greta out!
- Put them behind bars!

114
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:52,829
Mr. Roja, is it true that you know
where your wife is hiding?

115
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:53,996
[MAN] He's right.

116
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,832
I really don't know where my wife is.

117
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:58,543
[CAMERAS CLICKING]

118
00:06:58,626 --> 00:07:00,670
Once I find out,

119
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:03,047
I'll make sure

120
00:07:03,131 --> 00:07:05,299
that we'll be coordinating
with the authorities.

121
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:06,926
Liar!

122
00:07:07,009 --> 00:07:08,886
Bring your criminal wife out!

123
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,680
Put the Rojas behind bars!

124
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:13,015
[PROTESTORS]
Put the Rojas behind bars!

125
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:16,978
- [PROTESTOR 1] They shouldn't be free!
- [PROTESTOR 2] Criminals!

126
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:19,105
Please stop!

127
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:25,194
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:29,031
- Excuse me. Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

129
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,408
Excuse me, please.

130
00:07:37,915 --> 00:07:41,002
- You're wrong about them.
- [MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:07:41,085 --> 00:07:45,214
[SOBBING] Liam and Sir Magnus helped us.

132
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,633
They helped our family.

133
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:50,219
[CAMERAS CLICKING]

134
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:52,722
Liam,

135
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,932
thank you for saving my life.

136
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:57,393
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

137
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:59,937
[WOMAN] Is the kid telling the truth?

138
00:08:06,903 --> 00:08:10,781
Our family wouldn't still be alive
if not for the Rojas.

139
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:12,158
[CAMERAS CLICKING]

140
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:16,078
They risked their lives for us.

141
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,414
Especially Liam.

142
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,916
Thank you.

143
00:08:27,131 --> 00:08:29,133
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

144
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:31,010
[MAN] So they're kind.

145
00:08:31,093 --> 00:08:32,720
I didn't know they were kind.

146
00:08:32,803 --> 00:08:34,430
- That's true.
- Why are we protesting?

147
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,140
[WOMAN] They're good people.

148
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:42,396
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

149
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:46,234
<i>I'm so sorry, guys,</i>
<i>if I'm being emotional now.</i>

150
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:47,318
<i>But…</i>

151
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:50,863
<i>I just wanted to share that</i>

152
00:08:51,697 --> 00:08:53,908
<i>I wouldn't be here today</i>

153
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:58,412
<i>if it weren't for the people who saved us</i>
<i>from the hostage takers.</i>

154
00:08:58,496 --> 00:09:01,541
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

155
00:09:01,624 --> 00:09:03,501
<i>Liam Roja was one of them.</i>

156
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:08,297
<i>I know there are lots of people</i>
<i>bashing his family right now,</i>

157
00:09:08,381 --> 00:09:10,633
<i>but I was there.</i>

158
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:13,094
<i>I witnessed what he has done.</i>

159
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:18,391
<i>I saw how he risked his life</i>
<i>to save people.</i>

160
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,810
<i>Just like Maddie.</i>

161
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:23,688
<i>The little girl who's in the video.</i>

162
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,398
<i>She hugged Liam.</i>

163
00:09:26,857 --> 00:09:28,734
<i>It's viral right now.</i>

164
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:30,111
<i>But…</i>

165
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:36,117
<i>As much as Liam is a heroic person,</i>

166
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:39,704
<i>he couldn't save everyone.</i>

167
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:43,457
<i>He also needed help.</i>

168
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:46,168
<i>So…</i>

169
00:09:48,212 --> 00:09:51,048
<i>Shout out to you, Olsen Bonifacio.</i>

170
00:09:53,801 --> 00:09:56,929
<i>He's a security officer at La Playa Roja.</i>

171
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,056
<i>He saved a lot of people too.</i>

172
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:03,102
<i>Including me.</i>

173
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:04,312
<i>So,</i>

174
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:07,440
<i>special thanks to you, Olsen.</i>

175
00:10:09,817 --> 00:10:11,402
[ICE] That's my last vlog.

176
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:14,989
Really?

177
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:17,283
Why?

178
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,369
You just came back.

179
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:22,705
It already has a million views.

180
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:23,789
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

181
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:27,501
I'm going to concentrate
on my nursing degree.

182
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:29,253
Besides,

183
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:33,341
I've come to realize that
saving lives is my true purpose.

184
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:34,508
Mm.

185
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,846
You and Liam inspired me.

186
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:41,140
Especially you.

187
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:47,021
And it's what my mom wants.

188
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,149
For me to become a nurse.

189
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:54,320
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

190
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:56,113
Well, Ice,

191
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:59,825
I'm glad you've found your purpose.

192
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:06,290
You know I support you,
no matter what you choose to do.

193
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:11,295
Even if I'll be far away?

194
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:16,467
My cousin lives in Canada.

195
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:18,719
And

196
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:20,888
he's going to help me find
a job in Canada.

197
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:24,100
Everything that happened
on the island made me realize

198
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:26,894
how much I miss my mom.

199
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:30,898
She almost lost me, Olsen.

200
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:34,985
I know you understand that feeling.

201
00:11:37,238 --> 00:11:43,994
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,167
Ice.

203
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:56,298
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

204
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:57,967
I need to tell you something.

205
00:12:01,637 --> 00:12:02,763
I like you.

206
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:06,475
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

207
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:11,647
But I also want you to pursue your dreams.

208
00:12:13,607 --> 00:12:14,483
All right?

209
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:16,861
No matter how long it takes,

210
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,573
I will wait for you.

211
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:27,746
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:46,682
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

213
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:50,853
Then wait.

214
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:56,901
I promise you, Olsen…

215
00:12:58,777 --> 00:13:00,279
I will come back.

216
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,367
You better keep your promise.

217
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:12,458
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:13:28,098 --> 00:13:35,064
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

219
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:41,946
[MIKE] If you and your father
need anything, anything at all,

220
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:43,280
just say the word.

221
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:46,033
Having you here is enough.

222
00:13:46,116 --> 00:13:48,869
Thank you very much, Engineer, Architect.

223
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:50,871
- Mm.
- Maddie.

224
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:55,167
Thank you for believing in us
when no one else did.

225
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:56,627
[MINNIE SIGHS SOFTLY]

226
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:59,964
I really hope that your mom's okay,

227
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:02,925
and I pray that despite what's going on,

228
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,554
she's safe.

229
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:07,638
I hope so too.

230
00:14:09,265 --> 00:14:12,518
I can assure you, we're not hiding Mama.

231
00:14:13,435 --> 00:14:15,938
We also want justice for everyone.

232
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:20,192
But Liam?

233
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:23,529
Promise me you won't be in danger again.

234
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:28,158
I promise.

235
00:14:29,743 --> 00:14:36,417
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

236
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:50,055
You know, I've been telling
everyone the truth that I…

237
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:53,684
I really don't know
where Greta is to be found.

238
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:58,397
I understand
where your loyalty is, Magnus.

239
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:02,693
Of course, it's with Greta.

240
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:06,906
But what about us?

241
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:10,409
What about my father?

242
00:15:10,492 --> 00:15:12,453
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:14,830
What about the people who died?

244
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:17,833
What about the people they left behind?

245
00:15:19,543 --> 00:15:22,922
What about the people who suffered
because of your wife?

246
00:15:24,506 --> 00:15:25,549
Zero?

247
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:29,094
They get nothing?

248
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:36,810
Can your conscience handle
turning your back on us

249
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,147
just for your wife?

250
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:44,735
Or maybe what I should be asking is…

251
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,782
do you still have a conscience?

252
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:55,120
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

253
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:56,288
[SIGHS]

254
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:02,544
If you truly care about us…

255
00:16:05,089 --> 00:16:06,340
about me…

256
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:11,095
then give us peace.

257
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:15,140
Tell us where Greta is.

258
00:16:15,224 --> 00:16:18,519
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

259
00:16:18,602 --> 00:16:20,688
Magnus…

260
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,273
Magnus, please.

261
00:16:24,441 --> 00:16:26,068
I'm sorry, Wendy.

262
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:30,364
There's nothing I can tell you.

263
00:16:31,865 --> 00:16:33,200
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

264
00:16:35,744 --> 00:16:42,126
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:16:50,592 --> 00:16:56,890
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:17:00,728 --> 00:17:05,065
In the name of the Father, and of the Son,
and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

267
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:07,651
Thank you, Father.

268
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:13,949
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:19,079
[WENDY SQUEALS]

270
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:21,749
<i>- You're so amazing!</i>
- [OLSEN CHUCKLES]

271
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:23,667
<i>Let's celebrate. Come on.</i>

272
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:25,502
<i>- Okay, Grandpa.</i>
<i>- Let's celebrate.</i>

273
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:26,962
[OLSEN] <i>Thank you so much, Grandpa.</i>

274
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,381
<i>You've helped me so much. You know that.</i>

275
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:33,761
<i>Of course, you're my grandson. </i>[CHUCKLES]

276
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:35,679
<i>Can I join you?</i>

277
00:17:39,391 --> 00:17:40,559
<i>Mama!</i>

278
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,228
<i>Mama!</i>

279
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,776
<i>- Papa.</i>
<i>- Grandpa!</i>

280
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:50,319
[BEN] <i>Welcome back!</i>

281
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:56,867
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

282
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:58,744
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you very much.

283
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:02,122
- Auntie, I'll leave now.
- All right.

284
00:18:02,206 --> 00:18:04,208
- Olsen.
- Take care, Fin.

285
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:05,501
Thank you.

286
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,803
I'm trying to convince myself that

287
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:17,721
maybe

288
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:20,474
it's just sand in there.

289
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:25,312
Could be, right?

290
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:30,234
But it's not.

291
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:34,696
It really is Grandpa's ashes in there.

292
00:18:41,745 --> 00:18:44,039
I'm sorry, son.

293
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:47,042
For all the times I lied to you.

294
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:50,254
I just wanted to protect you.

295
00:18:50,337 --> 00:18:52,506
I was just thinking

296
00:18:52,589 --> 00:18:59,179
that maybe it was better for you to think
your father was a good man

297
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:03,475
than to grow up knowing who he really is.

298
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:06,478
That way, you wouldn't grow up
with hatred in your heart.

299
00:19:09,439 --> 00:19:11,984
Don't worry, Ma. I understand.

300
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:16,738
Especially now I know…

301
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:17,865
[CLEARS THROAT]

302
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:19,324
…who my real father is.

303
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:26,081
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:30,669
We have a lot of money.

305
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:32,004
Millions!

306
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:36,216
We should be staying at a five-star hotel.

307
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:40,137
Instead, we're hiding here like rats!

308
00:19:41,096 --> 00:19:43,307
The mission is not over yet.

309
00:19:44,808 --> 00:19:48,061
We need to get Boss Emil.
We need to get Mila!

310
00:19:49,229 --> 00:19:51,106
We'll get your father back, Leni.

311
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:52,649
Don't worry.

312
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:55,277
Even if we did manage to do it,

313
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,987
at what cost?

314
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:58,739
How many more are going to die?

315
00:19:59,656 --> 00:20:02,367
You're even putting Papa's life
on the line with your plan.

316
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,622
Leni.

317
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:10,626
We won't let anything happen
to your father.

318
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:14,087
We will help him get what he really wants.

319
00:20:14,171 --> 00:20:15,672
My sister, Ayen.

320
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,216
Ayen is who he wants.

321
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:19,927
Because if she'd really wanted to,

322
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:22,471
she would have come back to us
a long time ago.

323
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:26,099
You wouldn't understand.

324
00:20:26,975 --> 00:20:30,312
Fathers will never abandon their children.

325
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:32,189
We don't leave them.

326
00:20:32,272 --> 00:20:34,858
What do you know about being a father?

327
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:36,777
Isn't Olsen your son?

328
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:38,070
What did you do?

329
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:41,823
What proof do I have that he's my son?

330
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:43,951
His mother denied it, remember?

331
00:20:44,034 --> 00:20:50,624
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

332
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:05,055
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYS, SWELLS]

333
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:10,185
<i>Do you think Mama's at</i>
<i>the rest house on King's Road?</i>

334
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:13,563
<i>We'll have to do our best to convince her</i>
<i>to surrender to the police.</i>

335
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:15,148
<i>We know you're here, Greta.</i>

336
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:16,149
<i>Ma!</i>

337
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:19,987
[WENDY] <i>If you know where Greta is,</i>
<i>why don't you just tell the police?</i>

338
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:21,446
[OLSEN] <i>I want to make sure first, Ma.</i>

339
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:25,575
<i>Emil Padua's being taken</i>
<i>into police custody.</i>

340
00:21:26,201 --> 00:21:28,370
<i>Don't put me in jail with this bastard!</i>

341
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:30,247
<i>You are just like him, Jacinto.</i>

342
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:33,125
<i>Let's see if you'll make it out alive.</i>

343
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:38,547
[GUNSHOTS]

344
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:40,465
<i>Someone's here already.</i>

345
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:47,139
[OLSEN] <i>No one else knows</i>
<i>about this property.</i>

346
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:50,350
<i>I have a feeling Ma'am Greta is there.</i>

347
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:57,983
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
